The Osi Olubdan of Ibadanland, High Chief Rasidi Ladoja has said that all controversies surrounding the Chieftaincy and Enthronement of the next Olubada of Ibadanland have been resolved.
Chief Ladoja said this while briefing the newsmen on the outcome of a closed door meeting with the members of Olubadan in council had with the Executive Governor of the state, Engineer Seyi Makinde at the Government House Lodge, Agodi, Ibadan.
Chief Ladoja also affirmed the candidature of Otun Olubadan of Ibadan Land, High Chief Lekan Balogun as the next Olubadan of Ibadan, adding that the Ibadan high chiefs have resolved their differences and very united to install Chief Balogun as the next Olubadan of Ibadanland.
Among the members of Olubadan in Council that attended the Meeting, were; High Chief Lekan Balogun, High Chief Owolabi Olakuleyin, High Chief Gbadamosi Adebimpe, and High Chief Eddy Oyewole.
 
